[Student "S"]
{You don't want to make a Splinter Bid with a singleton King so you content yourself with a Jacoby 2NT bid. Partner rebids 4\D. What do you say next? 

The 4\D bid shows a 5-card \D suit. What you need to know now is how many Aces partner has. You bid 4NT and he answers 5\H.  

He has two Aces so you bid 6\S.}

